<h1>ANSWERS</h1>
			<div id = "post-ans" class = "post">
				<p>You may be falling on the wrong side of when the server rolls over between days - the day changes at midnight GMT (10 AM in Brisbane, 8 PM EST) so if you don't visit between 10 AM today and 10 AM tomorrow you won't have visited for 24 hours despite having visited once each day (eg. 9:30 AM today and say noon tomorrow).</p>

<p>Check out <a href="https://meta.stackexchange.com/questions/61007/consecutive-day-count-reset-this-morning">Consecutive Day count reset this morning</a> on MSO for a similar situation.</p>

<p>Also, just visiting the front page isn't always enough to make it count.</p>

